26/01/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The United States has asked Albania to intensify efforts to prevent illegal traffic of weapons of mass destruction, Albania's Foreign Affairs Ministry spokesman Agim Meza said Saturday (25 January).
Meza cited a letter by US Deputy Secretary of State Richard Armitage in which he urged the country to assist the International Atomic Energy Agency in its mission to stop the spread of nuclear weapons and their illegal production.
(ATA - 25/01/03)
